.TH NN 1 "January 2026" "nn 4.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nn \- fast note-taking CLI for engineers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nn
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fINAME\fR]
.br
.B nn
\fB\-T\fR \fITEMPLATE\fR [\fINAME\fR]
.br
.B nn
\fB\-a\fR "\fITEXT\fR"
.br
\fICOMMAND\fR | \fBnn \-i\fR [\fINAME\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nn
(New Note) is a fast, opinionated note-taking tool designed for engineers.
It creates markdown notes organized by date in a hierarchical folder structure.
.PP
Notes are stored in \fI~/journal/YYYY/MM/DD/\fR by default.
All notes include YAML frontmatter with metadata.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Creating Notes"
.TP
.B nn
Create or open today's journal.
.TP
.BI nn " NAME"
Create a named note in today's folder.
.TP
.BI \-T " TEMPLATE" "\fR [\fINAME\fR]"
.TQ
.BI \-\-template " TEMPLATE" "\fR [\fINAME\fR]"
Create note from template. See \fBTEMPLATES\fR section.
.TP
.BI \-a " TEXT"
.TQ
.BI \-\-append " TEXT"
Quick append to today's journal without opening editor.
.TP
.BI \-i " \fR[\fINAME\fR]"
.TQ
.BI \-\-stdin " \fR[\fINAME\fR]"
Pipe stdin to a note. Useful for capturing command output.
.SS "Navigation"
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yesterday
Open yesterday's journal.
.TP
.BR \-Y ", " \-\-tomorrow
Open tomorrow's journal (for prep notes).
.TP
.BI + N
.TQ
.BI \- N
Jump N days forward or back. E.g., \fBnn \-3\fR opens 3 days ago.
.SS "Browse & Search"
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
List today's notes.
.TP
.BI \-r " \fR[\fIN\fR]"
.TQ
.BI \-\-recent " \fR[\fIN\fR]"
List N most recent notes (default: 10).
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-open
Fuzzy find and open notes with fzf.
.TP
.BI \-s " TERM"
.TQ
.BI \-\-search " TERM"
Search note contents with grep or ripgrep.
.TP
.BI \-f " PATTERN"
.TQ
.BI \-\-find " PATTERN"
Find notes by filename pattern.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tree
Show directory tree of notes.
.TP
.B \-\-latest
Open most recently modified note.
.SS "Git Sync"
.TP
.B \-\-sync
Git add, commit, and push all changes.
.TP
.B \-\-git\-init
Initialize git repository in notes directory.
.SS "Utility"
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path
Print today's notes directory path.
.TP
.BI \-e " \fR[\fINAME\fR]"
.TQ
.BI \-\-view " \fR[\fINAME\fR]"
Open note in pager (read-only).
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-markdown
Display markdown syntax cheat sheet.
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Show note statistics and streak count.
.TP
.B \-\-completions
Output shell completions for bash and zsh.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-h ", " \-help ", " \-\-help ", " \-? ", " \-\-?
Show help message.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version number.
.SH TEMPLATES
Templates are pre-filled note formats. Use with \fB\-T\fR option.
.TP
.B journal
Daily journal with sections for mood, wins, blockers, and tomorrow's focus.
.TP
.B incident
Incident response: timeline, impact, status, mitigation steps.
.TP
.B postmortem
Post-incident review: 5 whys, action items, lessons learned.
.TP
.B oncall
On-call handoff: open issues, alerts fired, things to watch.
.TP
.B runbook
Operational runbook: prerequisites, steps, rollback, escalation.
.TP
.B standup
Daily standup: yesterday, today, blockers.
.TP
.B 1on1
One-on-one meeting notes.
.TP
.B meeting
General meeting: agenda, notes, decisions, action items.
.TP
.B retro
Sprint retrospective: went well, improve, action items.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NOTES_ROOT
Base directory for notes. Default: \fI$HOME/journal\fR
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor to use. Default: \fIvim\fR
.TP
.B PAGER
Pager for read-only view. Default: \fIless\fR
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/journal/
Default notes directory.
.TP
.I ~/journal/YYYY/MM/DD/
Date-organized subdirectories.
.TP
.I ~/journal/.latest
Symlink to most recently modified note.
.TP
.I ~/journal/.git/
Git repository (after \fB\-\-git\-init\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Create today's journal:
.RS
.nf
$ nn
.fi
.RE
.PP
Quick append without opening editor:
.RS
.nf
$ nn -a "deployed v2.3.1 to production"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create incident doc:
.RS
.nf
$ nn -T incident database-outage
.fi
.RE
.PP
Capture command output:
.RS
.nf
$ kubectl describe pod foo | nn -i pod-debug
.fi
.RE
.PP
Navigate to yesterday:
.RS
.nf
$ nn -y
.fi
.RE
.PP
Jump 3 days back:
.RS
.nf
$ nn -3
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search all notes:
.RS
.nf
$ nn -s "kubernetes"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Git sync:
.RS
.nf
$ nn --sync
.fi
.RE
